The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | New role for Mike, Greg 
                                                                                                                       7                                      New role for Mike, Greg 
            A STAFF REPORTER                            
	Calcutta: Two former Ashes captains  Mike Brearley of England and Australias Greg Chappell  have agreed to become International Cricket Council (ICC) ambassadors to help support Pakistan cricket and the Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) in the next year.         
	According to a media release, ICC chief executive Haroon Lorgat made the announcement during the historic neutral MCC Spirit of Cricket Test between Pakistan and Australia at Lords, on Thursday.         
	We are grateful to members of the ICC Pakistan Task Team who have worked extremely hard, under the leadership of ECB chairman Giles Clarke, to ensure they are able to play at international level, Lorgat said.                                                                                                                     
